1
00:00:00,140 --> 00:00:03,060
=The Crow Princess of Fortune=

2
00:00:03,060 --> 00:00:04,980
=Episode 5=

3
00:00:06,900 --> 00:00:08,539
(Fine. I'll do it for my father's sake.)

4
00:00:08,540 --> 00:00:10,060
(But...)

5
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:12,819
I'm so miserable.

6
00:00:12,820 --> 00:00:14,419
I thought that by following the Prince,

7
00:00:14,420 --> 00:00:16,099
Father could enjoy wealth and honor,

8
00:00:16,100 --> 00:00:17,539
and live the high life.

9
00:00:17,540 --> 00:00:19,779
But look? There isn't even anyone
to welcome us at the door.

10
00:00:19,780 --> 00:00:21,640
There are only two people
in the entire manor.

11
00:00:21,640 --> 00:00:23,580
One is hard of hearing,
and the other talks too much.

12
00:00:23,940 --> 00:00:25,760
Little Princess,
how can you say such things?

13
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:26,219
Exactly.

14
00:00:26,220 --> 00:00:27,379
I ain't wrong.

15
00:00:27,380 --> 00:00:28,699
This place is dirt poor.

16
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:31,060
Even the fish they serve is rotten.

17
00:00:32,420 --> 00:00:34,140
(Quick, play along with me.)

18
00:00:35,860 --> 00:00:38,979
How dare you!
I took you in out of kindness,

19
00:00:38,980 --> 00:00:41,660
yet I didn't expect you
to be so ungrateful.

20
00:00:42,020 --> 00:00:44,779
Dajun, bring me my sword.

21
00:00:44,780 --> 00:00:47,500
I'm going to finish off
this ingrate today.

22
00:00:48,020 --> 00:00:48,860
This...

23
00:00:48,940 --> 00:00:49,779
Yes.

24
00:00:49,780 --> 00:00:50,939
Calm down, Your Highness.

25
00:00:50,940 --> 00:00:52,219
You can't do that.

26
00:00:52,220 --> 00:00:54,099
She didn't mean it.

27
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:56,459
Crown Prince Uncle.

28
00:00:56,460 --> 00:00:59,059
Crown Prince Uncle, help me.

29
00:00:59,060 --> 00:01:00,539
I was just telling the truth.

30
00:01:00,540 --> 00:01:03,180
I don't want to lose my life.

31
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:07,099
He looks down on you.

32
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:09,460
So show him
what you're truly capable of.

33
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:10,899
Crown Prince Uncle,

34
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:13,820
do you really want to be
looked down on by a crippled prince?

35
00:01:14,820 --> 00:01:17,380
That's right, Xiao Heng.

36
00:01:17,620 --> 00:01:19,580
It's because
you're incompetent yourself.

37
00:01:21,140 --> 00:01:22,260
Little girl,

38
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:23,699
anything he can't give you,

39
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:25,740
I can give you.

40
00:01:29,780 --> 00:01:32,100
I reward you with this jade pendant.

41
00:01:34,220 --> 00:01:35,179
Crown Prince Uncle,

42
00:01:35,180 --> 00:01:36,899
I can tell you're a leader among men,

43
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:38,139
limitlessly wealthy,

44
00:01:38,140 --> 00:01:40,299
and someone who achieves great things.

45
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:42,459
Xiao Heng, you useless prince!

46
00:01:42,460 --> 00:01:45,259
Compared to the Crown Prince,
you're nothing.

47
00:01:45,260 --> 00:01:46,259
Nonsense.

48
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:48,020
It's just a jade pendant.

49
00:01:48,180 --> 00:01:49,859
Try asking him for something else.

50
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:51,020
See if he'll give it to you.

51
00:01:51,060 --> 00:01:52,139
Exactly.

52
00:01:52,140 --> 00:01:53,059
That's right.

53
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:54,420
Why wouldn't I?

54
00:01:56,980 --> 00:01:58,899
Here, gold leaves.

55
00:01:58,900 --> 00:02:00,940
Fifty of them.

56
00:02:03,180 --> 00:02:04,500
How boring.

57
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:09,420
I'll give you
this top-grade divine wood fan too.

58
00:02:11,940 --> 00:02:13,380
It's just average.

59
00:02:15,660 --> 00:02:18,740
I'll even give you
this premium bear-fur cloak.

60
00:02:20,220 --> 00:02:23,260
Take my red velvet belt.

61
00:02:24,940 --> 00:02:26,380
Little Princess, look.

62
00:02:27,940 --> 00:02:30,019
And my special-grade
deer-hide inner robe.

63
00:02:30,020 --> 00:02:32,140
Take it, just take it.
It's worth a hundred taels.

64
00:02:32,420 --> 00:02:32,979
That's it?

65
00:02:32,980 --> 00:02:34,660
Bring me my sword.

66
00:02:35,340 --> 00:02:38,259
This imperial black iron sword
is worth at least a thousand taels.

67
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:39,140
Take it.

68
00:02:40,220 --> 00:02:41,420
And this.

69
00:02:41,460 --> 00:02:42,339
This.

70
00:02:42,340 --> 00:02:43,780
And this.

71
00:02:43,820 --> 00:02:45,260
This too.

72
00:02:45,460 --> 00:02:46,900
I'm giving you this as well.

73
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:48,979
It's all gone.

74
00:02:48,980 --> 00:02:51,219
Everything's gone. What do you think?

75
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:53,619
I have nothing left on me now.

76
00:02:53,620 --> 00:02:55,619
Is there really nothing left?

77
00:02:55,620 --> 00:02:56,860
Nothing at all.

78
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:59,340
I can give you anything. How about that?

79
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:03,819
Can you?

80
00:03:03,820 --> 00:03:05,140
Of course, I can't.

81
00:03:05,780 --> 00:03:09,019
Because we were just playing you.

82
00:03:09,020 --> 00:03:12,180
Ha ha!

83
00:03:12,980 --> 00:03:14,020
What do you mean?

84
00:03:14,180 --> 00:03:14,859
Dajun.

85
00:03:14,860 --> 00:03:15,660
Present.

86
00:03:15,860 --> 00:03:17,840
- Close the doors and see our guest out.
- Close the doors and see our guest out.

87
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:18,419
Yes, Your Highness.

88
00:03:18,420 --> 00:03:19,699
Crown Prince, please.

89
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:21,059
What are you doing?

90
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:23,740
Go... Out you go.

91
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:27,200
(Prince Jing Manor)

92
00:03:28,940 --> 00:03:30,740
What a joke.

93
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:33,300
So,

94
00:03:33,620 --> 00:03:35,060
have I been "badger-gamed"?

95
00:03:36,860 --> 00:03:37,899
How did he end up like this?

96
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:39,260
I heard he was "badger-gamed."

97
00:03:42,260 --> 00:03:44,059
Xiao Heng, open the door.

98
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:44,899
You loser!

99
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,259
How dare you toy with me?

100
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:47,700
Open this door.

101
00:03:48,180 --> 00:03:49,659
You're just a defeated general.

102
00:03:49,660 --> 00:03:51,819
Your legs are crippled,
and your army is gone.

103
00:03:51,820 --> 00:03:54,460
Father wouldn't even spare you a glance.

104
00:03:55,180 --> 00:03:57,779
You might as well stay in
this ruined manor and wait to die.

105
00:03:57,780 --> 00:03:58,900
Just wait to die!

106
00:04:00,540 --> 00:04:02,179
My life

107
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:03,419
is not for others to decide.

108
00:04:03,420 --> 00:04:05,539
If you wish to decide for me,

109
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:07,660
you should first see
if you have what it takes.

110
00:04:28,580 --> 00:04:30,580
This one is for roast chicken.

111
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:32,940
This one is for candied haws.

112
00:04:33,260 --> 00:04:35,620
This one is for braised pork hock.

113
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:39,660
This one is for steamed sea bass.

114
00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:42,460
And this one...

115
00:04:47,940 --> 00:04:48,699
Sigh.

116
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:49,820
Forget it.

117
00:04:50,660 --> 00:04:52,779
This manor is too old.

118
00:04:52,780 --> 00:04:54,359
The rest of these

119
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:57,180
will all be used to fix up your nest.

120
00:04:59,660 --> 00:05:01,060
So much?

121
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:02,259
Don't you feel bad about it?

122
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:03,779
Why should I?

123
00:05:03,780 --> 00:05:05,579
You're my long-term meal ticket.

124
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:06,839
Only if you're alive

125
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:09,299
can I eat more and earn more.

126
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:10,979
This is called a long-term investment.

127
00:05:10,980 --> 00:05:13,899
As a Prince,
how can you not even understand this?

128
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:16,059
How about I teach you?

129
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:19,539
Alright, pay me tuition
on time every day.

130
00:05:19,540 --> 00:05:21,860
Half a pork hock per lesson.

131
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:23,020
Alright.

132
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:24,340
Your Highness!

133
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:36,519
♪Little lucky star,
twinkling with a wink at me♪

134
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:40,359
♪Every Chinese New Year day brings
the luckiest fortune slip♪

135
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:43,879
♪The God of Wealth favors me,
the Matchmaker ties red strings for me♪

136
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:46,840
♪With firecrackers going off,
good things keep coming one after another♪

137
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:51,359
♪Make a wish on the very first day
of the Chinese New Year♪

138
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:55,120
♪By the second day,
my belly's already round♪

139
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:58,519
♪Always talking about dieting,
but the chub never disappears♪

140
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:02,560
♪Good food brings joy
and happiness every single day♪

141
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:11,839
♪With lucky stars shining bright,
every year is filled with joy♪

142
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:15,479
♪I'm bringing blessings to everyone♪

143
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:19,199
♪Hands clasped together in greeting♪

144
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:22,839
♪May every family be sweet and happy♪

145
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:26,519
♪With lucky stars shining bright,
may everything go your way♪

146
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,439
♪Endlessly flowing♪

147
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:34,640
♪Good fortune♪
